Capstone Project Title:
UNWIND — A Constraint-Based Conversational System for Interrupting Narrative Drift
Project Overview
UNWIND is a deterministic, constraint-based conversational system designed to prevent narrative drift by redirecting users from story-level engagement to direct sensation-level contact.
Unlike adaptive or therapeutic chat systems, UNWIND deliberately limits flexibility. A state-driven interaction loop, pattern detection, and explicit safety gates are used to ensure the system does not reinforce narrative escalation, emotional rumination, or dependency.
The project explores whether constraint, rather than personalization, can improve reliability and safety in human–AI interaction.
